achings have made this \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":628,\"end\":816}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"sūtra\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":816,\"end\":821},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"c65438ed-99d8-45cc-bc87-72f8f617eea5\",\"uuid\":\"e3ea9cae-9640-4c30-a7d3-51a8a207b878\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" one of the favorites of \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":821,\"end\":846}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Mahāyāna\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":846,\"end\":854},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"99607e52-e246-4905-b531-6e6d7ccfd7b7\",\"uuid\":\"95b0c122-73c5-4366-8c9e-2e6318ef7e6d\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" literature.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":854,\"end\":866}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"15592a68-14bd-4450-97a7-933bfd74331d\",\"sort\":38,\"type\":\"acknowledgmentHeader\",\"label\":\"ac.\",\"alignments\":{}},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"heading\",\"attrs\":{\"level\":2,\"start\":0,\"end\":15,\"uuid\":\"9690aa08-31c7-4d5d-afe4-b3db3c0a7a22\",\"class\":\"section-title\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Acknowledgments\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":15}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"156851e7-b8ab-41bd-a219-126cd550bae0\",\"sort\":40,\"type\":\"acknowledgment\",\"label\":\"ac.1\",\"alignments\":{}},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":209,\"uuid\":\"a4f20e60-aa87-4aa5-9cf2-83aa41c03597\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Translated by Robert A. F. Thurman and first published, under the title \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":72}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"The Holy Teaching of Vimalakīrti: A Mahāyāna Scripture\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":72,\"end\":126},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"ee6af814-4307-4b9f-b2f7-600aeebe0d5f\",\"lang\":\"en\",\"type\":\"inlineTitle\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", by the Pennsylvania State University Press, University Park and London, in 1976. \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":126,\"end\":209}}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":209,\"end\":446,\"uuid\":\"b3e48cfe-da80-4b7e-9ad3-164b08054b82\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"This electronic edition for 84000: Translating the Words of the Buddha, with an abridged introduction and notes, and lightly edited under the supervision of Professor Thurman, is published by his kind permission as the copyright holder. \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":209,\"end\":446}}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":446,\"end\":488,\"uuid\":\"3438568e-093d-4f8f-8d6d-fe0ad683dfb5\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"From the Preface to the original edition:\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":446,\"end\":487},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":446,\"end\":487,\"uuid\":\"5e45bda5-3f9a-44b6-8a0a-7818dd63f7f0\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"emphasis\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":487,\"end\":488}}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":488,\"end\":1041,\"uuid\":\"6bcf4d6d-43a9-4e6c-be82-cf21310174a6\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"I sincerely thank my friend and benefactor, Dr. C. T. Shen, both for his sponsorship of the work and for his most helpful collaboration in the work of comparing the Tibetan and Chinese versions. We were sometimes joined in our round-table discussions by Drs. C. S. George, Tao-Tien Yi, F. S. K. Koo, and T. C. Tsao, whose helpful suggestions I gratefully acknowledge. My thanks also go to Ms. Yeshe Tsomo and Ms. Leah Zahler for their invaluable editorial assistance, and to Ms. Carole Schwager and the staff of The Pennsylvania State University Press. \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":488,\"end\":1041}}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1041,\"end\":1077,\"uuid\":\"c675b2a0-5f18-4438-9cb1-7f4ce9b6d015\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Preface to this electronic edition:\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1041,\"end\":1076},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1041,\"end\":1076,\"uuid\":\"a583cbc8-796b-4233-8a75-280f2bc982d6\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"emphasis\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1076,\"end\":1077}}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1077,\"end\":1302,\"uuid\":\"5d616f5a-6695-4dc1-8b4c-85ea547e8260\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"I earnestly thank Dzongsar Khyentse Rinpoche for his great efforts in creating the 84000: Translating the Words of the Buddha project, to present in English the many great works of the Buddha’s teachings freely to the world. \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1077,\"end\":1302}}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1302,\"end\":1822,\"uuid\":\"65cf80e6-dac6-490f-95a6-ae1fbcdade95\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"I also thank John Canti, of 84000, for his careful, creative, and very learned translating and editorial work on this electronic edition, without which this improved translation would not have materialized. I thank Mr. Patrick Alexander, of the Penn State University Press, who was the one who informed me that the copyright to my original translation done for the Institute for Advanced Studies of World Religions had reverted to me upon the termination of that Institute, to which I had previously conveyed my rights. \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1302,\"end\":1822}}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1822,\"end\":2172,\"uuid\":\"4c560777-43e2-4961-9144-56d2d13296d7\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"I intend to publish in print form a further update of that original version at a future time. Since there have been a number of free-floating electronic forms of this text on the internet for some years now, I am happy that the sūtra in its current revision is now available in the 84000 Reading Room, among the many other translations on that site. \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1822,\"end\":2172}}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2172,\"end\":2187,\"uuid\":\"8fc45c6c-1141-4bbc-bc5e-c86aa45cf543\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Sarva maṅgalam\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2172,\"end\":2186},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2172,\"end\":2186,\"uuid\":\"ff93775e-6327-4519-8175-b78395ef7460\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"!\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2186,\"end\":2187}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"a3ba4cdd-10eb-4a69-8296-b558da09269a\",\"sort\":53,\"type\":\"introductionHeader\",\"label\":\"i.\",\"alignments\":{}},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"heading\",\"attrs\":{\"level\":2,\"start\":0,\"end\":12,\"uuid\":\"974890ed-3fee-4bc7-82b1-2b9c9007c99a\",\"class\":\"section-title\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Introduction\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":12}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"43e82047-fa70-483c-8572-57d4674123fc\",\"sort\":55,\"type\":\"introduction\",\"label\":\"i.1\",\"alignments\":{}},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":482,\"uuid\":\"43e82047-fa70-483c-8572-57d4674123fc\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Among Buddhist \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":15}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"sūtras\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":15,\"end\":21},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"c65438ed-99d8-45cc-bc87-72f8f617eea5\",\"uuid\":\"09dfc9f1-1826-4090-8a75-bbfede23c1a9\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":21,\"end\":23}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"The Teaching of Vimalakīrti\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":23,\"end\":50},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"7a095743-61a2-410d-afa2-13946ac2966e\",\"lang\":\"en\",\"type\":\"inlineTitle\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" stands out like a masterfully faceted diamond, so located between the heaps of gold, silver, and pearls of the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":50,\"end\":162}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Transcendent ‌Wisdom\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":162,\"end\":182},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"e02dcef4-f52c-41e5-8933-8d54f9f5b271\",\"lang\":\"en\",\"type\":\"inlineTitle\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":182,\"end\":184}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Prajñā­pāramitā\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":184,\"end\":199},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"75992f50-46a1-41fd-af30-f3ce2c3e60f4\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"type\":\"inlineTitle\",\"start\":184,\"end\":0}},{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"9766cba6-2a43-4122-9ec8-5c4bd430c239\",\"uuid\":\"dcc5ff53-b222-4741-aca8-51dc129165da\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\") \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":199,\"end\":201}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Sūtras\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":201,\"end\":207},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"b1d30c80-873b-4a54-b0d8-f21718e48be3\",\"lang\":\"en\",\"type\":\"inlineTitle\",\"start\":201,\"end\":0}},{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"c65438ed-99d8-45cc-bc87-72f8f617eea5\",\"uuid\":\"d16413b0-3d0d-4d68-9052-dbb57bd1957b\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" and the array of sapphires, rubies, emeralds, and other gems of the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":207,\"end\":276}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"‌Buddha Garland\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":276,\"end\":291},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"58467b86-bfbb-4118-9f2e-18f118e54742\",\"lang\":\"en\",\"type\":\"inlineTitle\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":291,\"end\":293}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Buddhāvataṃsaka\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":293,\"end\":308},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"c26f5079-af67-4548-b824-6f8d81f9dbb7\",\"uuid\":\"9fb79390-4ccb-41bb-8c14-0f724a839b85\",\"toh\":null,\"start\":293,\"end\":0}},{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"046ca422-5049-49ed-a2b6-08fa41717585\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"type\":\"inlineTitle\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"), or \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":308,\"end\":314}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Inconceivable Liberation\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":314,\"end\":338},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"2b4294ad-a247-41c6-9c6a-308110c7be13\",\"lang\":\"en\",\"type\":\"inlineTitle\",\"start\":314,\"end\":0}},{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"9a3baeed-29d1-4683-bcd7-3c2f8f64c953\",\"uuid\":\"da73f472-9b36-4e89-9d20-122c83553e58\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":338,\"end\":340}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Acintyavimokṣa\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":340,\"end\":354},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"37278ac0-1a94-476b-a7bb-e5b3e1cc9e9f\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"type\":\"inlineTitle\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\") \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":354,\"end\":356}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Sūtras\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":356,\"end\":362},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"6fb35e48-adf8-4350-873b-99dd94e76fe5\",\"lang\":\"en\",\"type\":\"inlineTitle\",\"start\":356,\"end\":0}},{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"c65438ed-99d8-45cc-bc87-72f8f617eea5\",\"uuid\":\"305474ae-1792-424c-84df-b279197a2525\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" as to refract the radiances of all, beaming them forth to the beholder in a concentrated rainbow-beam of diamond light.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":362,\"end\":482}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"b0263ebb-1d2b-4196-9ff0-8ae4a361d546\",\"sort\":77,\"type\":\"introduction\",\"label\":\"i.2\",\"alignments\":{}},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":575,\"uuid\":\"b0263ebb-1d2b-4196-9ff0-8ae4a361d546\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"I elaborate upon this traditional metaphor here to convey a sense of how the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":77}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Vimalakīrti\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":77,\"end\":88},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"be71edf8-a95c-44e9-b800-a6657b904ec1\",\"lang\":\"en\",\"type\":\"inlineTitle\",\"start\":77,\"end\":0}},{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"b9ca12fb-e3be-4924-ad28-b09e52530acb\",\"uuid\":\"c07f4cd3-4636-4dfd-8466-009871f7bc96\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" is truly unique among Buddhist \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":88,\"end\":120}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"sūtras\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":120,\"end\":126},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"c65438ed-99d8-45cc-bc87-72f8f617eea5\",\"uuid\":\"fb682ba0-8f50-4967-9308-7561e4a744e2\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\". Unmatched in its content‍—a quintessence of \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":126,\"end\":172}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Mahāyāna\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":172,\"end\":180},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"99607e52-e246-4905-b531-6e6d7ccfd7b7\",\"uuid\":\"517176a9-33d2-42ee-a544-941f202a079e\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" doctrines, both of the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":180,\"end\":204}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"profound\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":204,\"end\":212},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":204,\"end\":212,\"uuid\":\"202c0346-40a4-4002-8cb8-745c18cf3f9a\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"emphasis\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" and of the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":212,\"end\":224}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"extensive\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":224,\"end\":233},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":224,\"end\":233,\"uuid\":\"a053c695-e526-444a-a37c-70cfeab7ff35\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"emphasis\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" categories‍—its aesthetic virtue, too, makes it an object of the connoisseur’s delight. This helps us understand how a hundred generations of \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":233,\"end\":376}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Mahāyāna\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":376,\"end\":384},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"99607e52-e246-4905-b531-6e6d7ccfd7b7\",\"uuid\":\"898ba345-4838-4a35-9f93-efe03e0a14bf\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" Buddhists in India, Central Asia, China, Japan, and South East Asia were disposed to study, revere, and enjoy this \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":384,\"end\":500}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"sūtra\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":500,\"end\":505},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"c65438ed-99d8-45cc-bc87-72f8f617eea5\",\"uuid\":\"843bfd9e-129d-456f-b6b4-f427c986a59a\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", finding enlightenment, inspiration, and the grace of pleasant humor.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":505,\"end\":575}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"db53565d-5ad3-4ce8-8eee-3dcfb872b8b1\",\"sort\":97,\"type\":\"introduction\",\"label\":\"i.3\",\"alignments\":{}},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":775,\"uuid\":\"db53565d-5ad3-4ce8-8eee-3dcfb872b8b1\",\"hasLeadingSpace\":true,\"leadingSpaceUuid\":\"3c9767a0-6dc4-49ca-a16e-2ce634cffb97\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"The \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":4}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"sūtra\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":4,\"end\":9},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"c65438ed-99d8-45cc-bc87-72f8f617eea5\",\"uuid\":\"510e80cc-7d1c-429e-9bac-7e5793678ab2\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" starts with the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":9,\"end\":26}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Buddha\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":26,\"end\":32},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"9b76e3ce-41f6-4da3-89a2-722141c90c1e\",\"uuid\":\"2e5956fc-a968-4e5c-8ba4-9c989e44af20\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", in the presence of a large assembly of monks and \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":32,\"end\":83}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"bodhisattvas\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":83,\"end\":95},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"c72eb4f3-700e-454d-996e-5ccdba29e6be\",\"uuid\":\"37b9093b-49f7-4dac-81da-e32ac396f645\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" gathered before him in \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":95,\"end\":119}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Āmrapālī\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":119,\"end\":127},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"837c2527-85cb-4a76-bf21-913ecb4a5d69\",\"uuid\":\"122cf07b-b164-4882-b59f-30ee37a9304f\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"’s grove outside \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":127,\"end\":144}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Vaiśālī\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":144,\"end\":151},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"e9c61804-d922-4a99-88ea-836faa6fd3c4\",\"uuid\":\"8428691b-53d5-44cc-b78e-5ef0b265de42\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", receiving offerings from five hundred youths from the city, headed by the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":151,\"end\":227}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Licchavi\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":227,\"end\":235},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"33770a73-e8ab-4ffb-9409-eb25bda5915d\",\"uuid\":\"1ec27e29-8047-4673-b65f-be7c79363d6f\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":235,\"end\":236}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"bodhisattva\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":236,\"end\":247},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"c72eb4f3-700e-454d-996e-5ccdba29e6be\",\"uuid\":\"81bd9cf4-059a-4573-a896-ffb6defeb9df\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":247,\"end\":248}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Ratnākara\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":248,\"end\":257},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"2f400df3-fb3c-4bd3-85ce-4b223afd1aad\",\"uuid\":\"59a16b08-eef3-4c08-b41d-d8ba28e9bd22\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", and in response revealing the entire universe as a vast \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":257,\"end\":315}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"buddhafield\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":315,\"end\":326},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"1e5e85e8-4767-46b1-874e-5f1396a67ee6\",\"uuid\":\"73a70dea-aba3-4025-8c17-23de4a2d286e\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" in a miraculous display, seen by all present. After pronouncing a notable praise to the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":326,\"end\":415}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Buddha\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":415,\"end\":421},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"9b76e3ce-41f6-4da3-89a2-722141c90c1e\",\"uuid\":\"060543fd-f2c7-4b68-a69c-65741b3cd9df\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" in verse, \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":421,\"end\":432}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Ratnākara\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":432,\"end\":441},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"2f400df3-fb3c-4bd3-85ce-4b223afd1aad\",\"uuid\":\"822b2e0a-8ec9-4a8b-97af-50394b878e19\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" asks him to explain what is meant by a \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":441,\"end\":481}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"bodhisattva\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":481,\"end\":492},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"c72eb4f3-700e-454d-996e-5ccdba29e6be\",\"uuid\":\"3123dcd0-cf86-4e88-9519-42771abdd01a\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" purifying his \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":492,\"end\":507}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"buddhafield\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":507,\"end\":518},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"1e5e85e8-4767-46b1-874e-5f1396a67ee6\",\"uuid\":\"2fafbb77-9c1c-4f68-97e6-e32a74b18b97\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\". The \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":518,\"end\":524}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Buddha\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":524,\"end\":530},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"9b76e3ce-41f6-4da3-89a2-722141c90c1e\",\"uuid\":\"0ded0021-c6bd-45fb-bb16-e5868ff0ea71\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"’s response to this request, together with further descriptions in the fifth, ninth, tenth, and eleventh chapters, constitute one of the most complete and profound teachings on the subject of \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":530,\"end\":722}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"buddhafields\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":722,\"end\":734},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"1e5e85e8-4767-46b1-874e-5f1396a67ee6\",\"uuid\":\"80b30f4a-bfa2-41b9-9660-c487462b0bb3\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" to be found in the canonical literature.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":734,\"end\":775}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"ee12b290-7088-441d-9909-02587af47dba\",\"sort\":129,\"type\":\"introduction\",\"label\":\"i.4\",\"alignments\":{}},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":911,\"uuid\":\"ee12b290-7088-441d-9909-02587af47dba\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"The second chapter introduces the great \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":40}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Licchavi\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":40,\"end\":48},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"33770a73-e8ab-4ffb-9409-eb25bda5915d\",\"uuid\":\"81610471-c384-4710-9da7-b2f6d6e461a1\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":48,\"end\":49}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"bodhisattva\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":49,\"end\":60},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"c72eb4f3-700e-454d-996e-5ccdba29e6be\",\"uuid\":\"8f064666-e1be-4238-9505-ec0e3fdd5b3f\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":60,\"end\":61}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Vimalakīrti\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":61,\"end\":72},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"b9ca12fb-e3be-4924-ad28-b09e52530acb\",\"uuid\":\"417da0bd-6fdf-4c81-bb94-f3e30ab36253\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", master of the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":72,\"end\":88}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"liberative art\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":88,\"end\":102},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"7c541c84-ac9d-49ce-92dc-9b1f6912648d\",\"uuid\":\"7dd1ddef-fe50-460c-a9df-4480a9a6eaa0\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", who lives as a \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":102,\"end\":119}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"layman\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":119,\"end\":125},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"441162aa-6112-465c-96b1-bf951ed9d5a3\",\"uuid\":\"05fab854-c257-41b3-86c7-505c8c14a58c\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" but transcends all categorization. Manifesting himself as if sick, he teaches all the notables and citizens of \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":125,\"end\":237}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Vaiśālī\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":237,\"end\":244},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"e9c61804-d922-4a99-88ea-836faa6fd3c4\",\"uuid\":\"bc44a373-ac5a-4a43-8f2f-156106fe1231\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", as they come to inquire about his health, on the insubstantial and unsatisfactory nature of the ordinary body, and compares it to the body of a \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":244,\"end\":390}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"tathāgata\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":390,\"end\":399},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"e708dad0-3dd7-49b0-8de3-b2e34b3f8d08\",\"uuid\":\"d8c002f2-6776-47ce-87db-cafd8f9f9847\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\". In the third chapter, the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":399,\"end\":427}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Buddha\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":427,\"end\":433},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"9b76e3ce-41f6-4da3-89a2-722141c90c1e\",\"uuid\":\"140bf10c-2f8d-4423-aa59-19d3cf46f4f7\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" asks his principal disciples, one by one, to visit \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":433,\"end\":485}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Vimalakīrti\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":485,\"end\":496},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"b9ca12fb-e3be-4924-ad28-b09e52530acb\",\"uuid\":\"87bba188-adee-45ce-b502-a173be115f35\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" on his sickbed. All of them in turn, however‍—first the great disciples, and then the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":496,\"end\":583}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"bodhisattvas\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":583,\"end\":595},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"c72eb4f3-700e-454d-996e-5ccdba29e6be\",\"uuid\":\"1c9e4329-bd1d-4c78-b8f8-39d580b42ad7\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"‍—feel reluctant to do so and decline on the grounds that previous encounters with him (recounted in detail) have left them astonished and somewhat discomfited by the profundity and transcendent nature of his \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":595,\"end\":804}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"views\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":804,\"end\":809},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"706840df-0c20-4c5d-94a4-6b4383506ee4\",\"uuid\":\"5af56389-832b-41cf-8933-30d83fb2ced6\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", often on topics or practices of which they had themselves hitherto been considered peerless masters.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":809,\"end\":911}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"bf6cd6af-51d8-4a95-b76a-6f929bc944ec\",\"sort\":153,\"type\":\"introduction\",\"label\":\"i.5\",\"alignments\":{}},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":1395,\"uuid\":\"bf6cd6af-51d8-4a95-b76a-6f929bc944ec\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Mañjuśrī\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":8},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"10b56931-f8ef-48df-9532-76c888687d0f\",\"uuid\":\"658aa490-ff46-4ed5-8431-8cef8a59bc8b\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\"