81bca268e7d1\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\". This accords with the degree of attainment of the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":485,\"end\":537}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"bodhisattva\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":537,\"end\":548},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"c72eb4f3-700e-454d-996e-5ccdba29e6be\",\"uuid\":\"59af2c41-2372-4fde-acac-4f7707f3ba87\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", so frequently reached by \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":548,\"end\":575}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Vimalakīrti\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":575,\"end\":586},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"b9ca12fb-e3be-4924-ad28-b09e52530acb\",\"uuid\":\"9e567868-e590-4f56-8a8f-704897ca1a21\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"’s audiences, called “the tolerance of the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":586,\"end\":629}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"birthlessness\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":629,\"end\":642},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"4031b212-ede8-469d-abc0-058f224db7a7\",\"uuid\":\"7592ee81-0fad-4a19-beb5-1b3490b36191\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" of all things” (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":642,\"end\":659}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"anutpattika­dharma­kṣānti\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":659,\"end\":684},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":659,\"end\":684,\"uuid\":\"f9d7a40a-6d42-445f-b438-07e1d8d695e5\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"). It is extremely significant that the term “tolerance” (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":684,\"end\":742}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"kṣānti\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":742,\"end\":748},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":742,\"end\":748,\"uuid\":\"2f5b057f-3b42-4cd2-90f0-31a6ab30695b\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\") is used here, rather than “conviction,” “understanding,” or “realization”; it emphasizes the fact that where the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":748,\"end\":863}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ultimate\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":863,\"end\":871},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"784c8158-9e46-4484-9152-e0d06cd46afc\",\"uuid\":\"d6a00b2c-b0ae-42c5-b11e-17d4fdb43b80\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" is concerned, the mind is unable to grasp anything in the pattern of dualistic knowledge, for there is no finite object in this case and only relative objects can be grasped with relative certainty in the mundane sense. Yet that is not to say that the student’s task is to simply put a label of “\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":871,\"end\":1168}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"inconceivability\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1168,\"end\":1184},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"dc39b632-2a80-43b2-8eec-3bd2a37aa05c\",\"uuid\":\"38b9d8a9-a639-4d49-b554-8c3e9f609934\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"” on all things and rest complacent with a sense of having reached a high state. Indeed, there are three stages of this tolerance: the verbal (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1184,\"end\":1327}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ghoṣānugā\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1327,\"end\":1336},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1327,\"end\":1336,\"uuid\":\"caa9950d-6ff6-40e3-b89a-d8ba0c20ae02\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"), conforming (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1336,\"end\":1351}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"anulomikī\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1351,\"end\":1360},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1351,\"end\":1360,\"uuid\":\"68e597d8-6887-47e5-8fa9-9963ead3c8b9\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"), and true \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1360,\"end\":1372}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"tolerance of the birthlessness of things\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1372,\"end\":1412},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"d576fbe3-9011-4ae4-9a17-b7c8a391981a\",\"uuid\":\"bfd18460-7021-44c9-b8e9-891055bd0678\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\". This indicates the difficulty of attainment of true tolerance, which occurs only at the eighth stage of bodhisattvahood.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1412,\"end\":1534},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"endNoteLink\",\"attrs\":{\"notes\":[{\"endNote\":\"e14c1f29-bda1-4227-9eee-e5f8c76f9453\",\"label\":\"2\",\"uuid\":\"2e5ae978-d3d6-45d5-8688-f8d32d47c745\",\"start\":1534,\"end\":1534,\"location\":\"end\",\"toh\":null}]}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1534,\"end\":1535}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Inconceivability\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1535,\"end\":1551},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"dc39b632-2a80-43b2-8eec-3bd2a37aa05c\",\"uuid\":\"904457f1-5aac-414c-ba82-db590a3600a8\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" as a verbal concept is only a principle to be applied to the mind, just like the verbal concept of \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1551,\"end\":1651}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"voidness\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1651,\"end\":1659},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"e74ef65c-8fc8-4dbf-9bba-7326d6b5d34d\",\"uuid\":\"d0cc6e80-aada-4307-9723-a002d705e495\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", or even of infinity.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1659,\"end\":1681}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"5a69ee01-801e-423e-83f5-ac828b09c235\",\"sort\":397,\"type\":\"introduction\",\"label\":\"i.10\",\"alignments\":{}},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":577,\"uuid\":\"5a69ee01-801e-423e-83f5-ac828b09c235\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"When we reflect intensively on any of these concepts, our minds open gradually in an ever widening sphere whose limits proceed from preconceived limitation to preconceived limitation. We discover to our surprise that there is always something further, and we logically discard the possibility of any limit being \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":312}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ultimate\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":312,\"end\":320},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"784c8158-9e46-4484-9152-e0d06cd46afc\",\"uuid\":\"42207808-eac0-4074-a30a-1fbda87459ff\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" because any limit serves as the near boundary of the next larger space or dimension or time. If we adhere rigorously to this process, we soon find ourselves lost in the stars, as it were, with less and less security about ever having started from anywhere.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":320,\"end\":577}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"25365da9-ef70-482b-930e-9501f5d362bd\",\"sort\":401,\"type\":\"introduction\",\"label\":\"i.11\",\"alignments\":{}},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":457,\"uuid\":\"25365da9-ef70-482b-930e-9501f5d362bd\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"The \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":4}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Buddha\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":4,\"end\":10},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"9b76e3ce-41f6-4da3-89a2-722141c90c1e\",\"uuid\":\"8213d309-67ce-4f81-9ac3-0bb9329aca31\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" gave this type of deepest teaching only to disciples able to deal with it. \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":10,\"end\":86}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Nāgārjuna\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":86,\"end\":95},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"68714aab-998c-4cd0-89e6-90509f6dcc76\",\"uuid\":\"746d2459-7dca-48d0-8342-8f6fda3f87c1\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" himself rarely spelled it out explicitly, restricting himself to providing the means whereby the disciplined intellect can strip away its own \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":95,\"end\":238}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"conceptualizations\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":238,\"end\":256},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"9f1b9148-fd02-40f8-963c-c5aee1733bf6\",\"uuid\":\"77ef7826-4a30-4a41-8936-3279344e12f9\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" and habitual notions. But \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":256,\"end\":283}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Vimalakīrti\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":283,\"end\":294},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"b9ca12fb-e3be-4924-ad28-b09e52530acb\",\"uuid\":\"91648155-e3fb-4442-88aa-013e85423eff\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" felt that such a message should be available to a much larger circle of people, for he expressed himself definitively on all occasions, as recorded in this \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":294,\"end\":451}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"sūtra\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":451,\"end\":456},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"c65438ed-99d8-45cc-bc87-72f8f617eea5\",\"uuid\":\"8d72b0ae-f624-45c8-8126-ecf9af63e5e6\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\".\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":456,\"end\":457}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"52791eb6-2922-4035-8704-d7997362325e\",\"sort\":415,\"type\":\"introduction\",\"label\":\"i.12\",\"alignments\":{}},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":1541,\"uuid\":\"52791eb6-2922-4035-8704-d7997362325e\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"The main technique \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":19}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Vimalakīrti\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":19,\"end\":30},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"b9ca12fb-e3be-4924-ad28-b09e52530acb\",\"uuid\":\"ecade370-8ded-4604-8d83-ffca69e8ce72\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" uses that is of interest here‍—dichotomy‍—is found in his discourse, which relates to another alternative title of the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":30,\"end\":150}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"sūtra\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":150,\"end\":155},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"c65438ed-99d8-45cc-bc87-72f8f617eea5\",\"uuid\":\"c5d4bb78-58f0-4f13-bb3a-71d81734bc0b\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", “\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":155,\"end\":158}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Reconciliation of Dichotomies\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":158,\"end\":187},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"b1f05db9-7380-4a8c-b8c2-ff2145a720b9\",\"uuid\":\"423505ad-ec68-4770-a875-7da7f81f949f\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"” (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":187,\"end\":190}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Yamaka­puṭa­vyatyasta­nihāra\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":190,\"end\":218},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"84f564b7-0319-4202-9f60-3c3f2f679842\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"type\":\"inlineTitle\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\").\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":218,\"end\":220},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"endNoteLink\",\"attrs\":{\"notes\":[{\"endNote\":\"44a4303f-1f72-4740-a2f4-7e68db029e26\",\"label\":\"3\",\"uuid\":\"f4afcc7e-2c8f-49c3-bfa3-abf750b7f908\",\"start\":220,\"end\":220,\"location\":\"end\",\"toh\":null}]}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" This is in keeping with the traditional method of the Middle Way masters, who had great skill in pitting polar opposites against each other to eliminate the fixedness of each and to free the mind of the student who applies himself to the polarities to open into a middle ground of reality beyond concepts. The \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":220,\"end\":531}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"mahāsiddhas\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":531,\"end\":542},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"aa77fe0c-f103-4bce-bb23-2bc3d416ca17\",\"uuid\":\"4fe5e1ee-35f4-4589-827b-0c6a64a38e3c\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" of first-millennium India refined this art to a consummate degree in their songs and extraordinary deeds, and the Great \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":542,\"end\":663}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Ch’an\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":663,\"end\":668},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"a289b9ae-5d56-46bd-9a95-0227c18b3226\",\"uuid\":\"007a3aa4-cd56-4742-a96f-c5d675fec6a1\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" and Zen Masters wielded the same “double-edged sword” in their earthshaking statements and their illuminating activities. The singular quality of such teachers’ use of dichotomies lies in the fact that they relate them to the actual practice of the hearers, forcing them to integrate them in their minds and actions. Thus, they expect them to be liberated inconceivably, while being totally engaged in the work of helping other living beings. They recommend their full cultivation of \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":668,\"end\":1153}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"great love\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1153,\"end\":1163},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"c1233550-43a1-4be4-9029-37b7e4e3f573\",\"uuid\":\"0e7b6ff6-6b82-48ad-80b4-e758340d7b61\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" and \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1163,\"end\":1168}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"great compassion\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1168,\"end\":1184},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"dc1f3a82-a37b-47bc-a900-9c62a98401cb\",\"uuid\":\"e3a36595-1afe-40dc-88ba-799c551dd409\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" while maintaining total awareness of the total absence of any such thing as a living being, a suffering being, a being in bondage. In short, they show the way to the full \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1184,\"end\":1356}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"nonduality\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1356,\"end\":1366},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"5bcad558-679e-41c8-a730-6e36945799b6\",\"uuid\":\"c244bf65-bb84-48cd-98b5-81909c179994\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" of \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1366,\"end\":1370}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"wisdom\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1370,\"end\":1376},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"38971298-6f62-48f0-b271-36261568d441\",\"uuid\":\"3aeffffd-2596-43a3-a9c7-fe5c9ab0b063\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" and \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1376,\"end\":1381}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"great compassion\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1381,\"end\":1397},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"dc1f3a82-a37b-47bc-a900-9c62a98401cb\",\"uuid\":\"d9b4545b-4a15-4494-ae00-f69826d27dba\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", the latter being expressed as skill in \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1397,\"end\":1438}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"liberative art\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1438,\"end\":1452},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"7c541c84-ac9d-49ce-92dc-9b1f6912648d\",\"uuid\":\"06546c7e-d42b-47a4-bba3-8a3677c9f011\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"‍—the integrated approach acknowledged by all the masters as the essence of the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1452,\"end\":1532}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Mahāyāna\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1532,\"end\":1540},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"99607e52-e246-4905-b531-6e6d7ccfd7b7\",\"uuid\":\"71736825-b7e3-47f1-a781-b4454b99c009\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\".\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1540,\"end\":1541}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"4ae909c4-a466-4f56-9806-4b5ff6bd9ba3\",\"sort\":445,\"type\":\"introduction\",\"label\":\"i.13\",\"alignments\":{}},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":535,\"uuid\":\"4ae909c4-a466-4f56-9806-4b5ff6bd9ba3\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Vimalakīrti\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":11},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"b9ca12fb-e3be-4924-ad28-b09e52530acb\",\"uuid\":\"f742f43b-169d-42d2-84c4-f3de1b50a969\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"’s \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":11,\"end\":14}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"reconciliation of dichotomies\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":14,\"end\":43},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"b1f05db9-7380-4a8c-b8c2-ff2145a720b9\",\"uuid\":\"d11fc777-1e1c-4322-9e3f-5667fec224a0\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" is so thoroughgoing that he shocks the disciples by his advocacy of the most horrible things as being part of the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":43,\"end\":158}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"bodhisattva\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":158,\"end\":169},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"c72eb4f3-700e-454d-996e-5ccdba29e6be\",\"uuid\":\"fa653d40-c8f1-44b4-80bc-18c9f5eade06\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"’s path. The \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":169,\"end\":182}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"bodhisattva\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":182,\"end\":193},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"c72eb4f3-700e-454d-996e-5ccdba29e6be\",\"uuid\":\"1fd7722d-d5e4-4517-b880-057534a9e6a7\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" may commit the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":193,\"end\":209}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"five deadly sins\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":209,\"end\":225},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"b3f27308-d8e9-4edd-b1de-2bb77c99ef3a\",\"uuid\":\"21b90da1-e696-488a-9c35-ad24266c15b9\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", follow the false \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":225,\"end\":244}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"outsider\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":244,\"end\":252},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"b121c9a5-7c63-4bc5-be7a-4f7ac29b7113\",\"uuid\":\"c5a75f7c-abaf-4ae4-9546-3aaa0e65076a\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" teachings, entertain the sixty-two false \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":252,\"end\":294}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"views\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":294,\"end\":299},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"706840df-0c20-4c5d-94a4-6b4383506ee4\",\"uuid\":\"72d7108e-2b91-4743-85eb-5499d1083f7d\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", consort with all the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":299,\"end\":322}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"passions\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":322,\"end\":330},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"2370c8e3-79cc-4eab-bc82-33939081f558\",\"uuid\":\"010c6afc-e791-4d36-bfeb-d9af2f7ceadb\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", and so on. Even the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":330,\"end\":352}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"māras\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":352,\"end\":357},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"dc91f42f-fab1-4b12-8cc4-98af048dd264\",\"uuid\":\"f388eb3f-b1e3-4a23-bf67-9b782a8a30ac\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", or devils, that plague the various universes are said to be \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":357,\"end\":419}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"bodhisattvas\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":419,\"end\":431},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"c72eb4f3-700e-454d-996e-5ccdba29e6be\",\"uuid\":\"afa78ef4-8cc0-4209-b2ee-97c1308a64a6\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" dwelling in \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":431,\"end\":444}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"inconceivable liberation\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":444,\"end\":468},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"9a3baeed-29d1-4683-bcd7-3c2f8f64c953\",\"uuid\":\"1b0aca33-82f5-4a69-a090-80c58fca15ca\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"‍—playing the devil, as it were, in order to develop living beings.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":468,\"end\":535}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"42361cd6-1ee2-4db2-a1a4-50323649b665\",\"sort\":468,\"type\":\"introduction\",\"label\":\"i.14\",\"alignments\":{}},\"content