:\"end\",\"toh\":null}]}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" all these lend the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1686,\"end\":1706}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"sūtra\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1706,\"end\":1711},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"c65438ed-99d8-45cc-bc87-72f8f617eea5\",\"uuid\":\"2546c0c3-37d0-4de5-8044-e7919422f659\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" a certain aura of \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1711,\"end\":1730}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"tantra\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1730,\"end\":1736},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"140c4504-5fe9-4a99-b7e9-b25cb2395c1a\",\"uuid\":\"797ba5dd-c623-45aa-a22d-56b1b582c4ee\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\". Whatever the “historical” relationship may be, there is no doubt that the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1736,\"end\":1812}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"mahāsiddhas\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1812,\"end\":1823},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"aa77fe0c-f103-4bce-bb23-2bc3d416ca17\",\"uuid\":\"be0f217e-8081-4078-97af-9f199bacbaa1\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" of later times would have felt at home in the house of \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1823,\"end\":1879}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Vimalakīrti\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1879,\"end\":1890},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"b9ca12fb-e3be-4924-ad28-b09e52530acb\",\"uuid\":\"2e55ab12-9c19-44ef-b582-1e52c696cabb\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\".\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1890,\"end\":1891}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"9f59f0bc-5f2a-4092-9528-b3710786c35b\",\"sort\":553,\"type\":\"introduction\",\"label\":\"i.15\",\"alignments\":{}},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":1334,\"uuid\":\"9f59f0bc-5f2a-4092-9528-b3710786c35b\",\"hasLeadingSpace\":true,\"leadingSpaceUuid\":\"66b822c2-d9cf-48a1-b149-aec607ad086f\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Nothing concrete is known about the “original text” of the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":59}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Vimala­kīrti­nirdeśa\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":59,\"end\":79},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"586f7012-d5fb-43b5-8a6a-ae64f7f59c27\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"type\":\"inlineTitle\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\". It purports to record events that took place during Gautama \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":79,\"end\":141}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Buddha\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":141,\"end\":147},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"9b76e3ce-41f6-4da3-89a2-722141c90c1e\",\"uuid\":\"7776a25a-0578-43f5-959e-286ea1a712f1\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"’s time (sixth to fifth century B.C.), but no text was apparent in India until after \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":147,\"end\":232}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Nāgārjuna\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":232,\"end\":241},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"68714aab-998c-4cd0-89e6-90509f6dcc76\",\"uuid\":\"66c261dd-18ff-4ea5-825f-b6e7ee9756fd\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" (c. first century B.C. to first century A.D.) had revived the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":241,\"end\":304}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Mahāyāna\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":304,\"end\":312},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"99607e52-e246-4905-b531-6e6d7ccfd7b7\",\"uuid\":\"3da75ca7-441e-4659-a756-13a751546635\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" traditions, discovering the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":312,\"end\":341}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Mahāyāna\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":341,\"end\":349},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"99607e52-e246-4905-b531-6e6d7ccfd7b7\",\"uuid\":\"1ed0b014-85b9-4977-b83b-f61809d213fb\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" Sanskrit \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":349,\"end\":359}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"sūtras\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":359,\"end\":365},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"c65438ed-99d8-45cc-bc87-72f8f617eea5\",\"uuid\":\"f8b03002-dcc5-413e-a510-bf744db5243d\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":365,\"end\":371}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Vimalakīrti\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":371,\"end\":382},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"32b77cec-2394-4f8e-aa99-3f390b1e54b7\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"type\":\"inlineTitle\",\"start\":371,\"end\":0}},{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"b9ca12fb-e3be-4924-ad28-b09e52530acb\",\"uuid\":\"8720ed38-ec4e-40cb-a617-dc3fab93d15a\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" text among them. This text was subsequently translated into Chinese seven different times, starting in the second century with Yan Fodiao\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":382,\"end\":520},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"endNoteLink\",\"attrs\":{\"notes\":[{\"endNote\":\"45312eee-52cc-488c-a67a-6ded82f100a8\",\"label\":\"11\",\"uuid\":\"5a2838e8-083b-4ead-9844-c19861c9ad3c\",\"start\":520,\"end\":520,\"location\":\"end\",\"toh\":null}]}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" (A.D. 188), the version of \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":520,\"end\":548}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Kumārajīva\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":548,\"end\":558},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"05d4dcc1-b553-4d8a-b913-3d42e28773e0\",\"uuid\":\"39bd5e44-f5d9-49e4-b698-912cef7c2c7c\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" (A.D. 406) being the most popular, and that of \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":558,\"end\":606}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Xuanzang\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":606,\"end\":614},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"d4a6a09d-8d75-48cd-91f4-20308ea589fb\",\"uuid\":\"29c17469-d400-4776-b126-fa611ebcd2dd\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" (A.D. 650) the most technically accurate. It was translated into Tibetan at least twice, the definitive version completed in the early ninth century by the well-known Tibetan translator \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":614,\"end\":801}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Chönyi Tsültrim\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":801,\"end\":816},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"34f0e6a4-28b4-49d9-ae71-234c4fa63529\",\"uuid\":\"50989f69-c8ec-4f3b-8fba-001f1fc213eb\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":816,\"end\":818}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"chos nyid tshul khrims\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":818,\"end\":840},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":818,\"end\":840,\"uuid\":\"813971bf-e6a6-445f-96e5-eeee35b4a1d8\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"), also known as Dharmatāśīla, who was one of the compilers of the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":840,\"end\":907}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Mahāvyutpatti\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":907,\"end\":920},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"7e16e90d-9e8c-4d2e-862a-ddb8d0436fd7\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"type\":\"inlineTitle\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\".\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":920,\"end\":921},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"endNoteLink\",\"attrs\":{\"notes\":[{\"endNote\":\"000bce1f-49be-4a4e-8ab5-926dd238b12b\",\"label\":\"12\",\"uuid\":\"479532c7-9743-4722-96b4-592c91389693\",\"start\":921,\"end\":921,\"location\":\"end\",\"toh\":null}]}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" It was also translated into Sogdian, Khotanese, and Uighur. For many years it was thought that all Sanskrit texts of the work had been lost, except for some fragments quoted in \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":921,\"end\":1099}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Mahāyāna\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1099,\"end\":1107},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"99607e52-e246-4905-b531-6e6d7ccfd7b7\",\"uuid\":\"a7c40073-444e-4e96-95f2-ec3a50bbfdf4\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" philosophical works. In 1998, however, a Sanskrit manuscript was found in the Potala Palace, Lhasa, of which edited versions were published in 2004 and 2006 by the Taishō University Study Group on Sanskrit Buddhist Literature.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1107,\"end\":1334},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"endNoteLink\",\"attrs\":{\"notes\":[{\"endNote\":\"046975d3-8a0e-4a4b-9eff-a0965892f948\",\"label\":\"13\",\"uuid\":\"1f069bf4-21a2-4890-9509-147a7e72f28f\",\"start\":1334,\"end\":1334,\"location\":\"end\",\"toh\":null}]}}]}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"54a5faac-00c4-4240-8c45-756db32a0620\",\"sort\":586,\"type\":\"introduction\",\"label\":\"i.16\",\"alignments\":{}},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":412,\"uuid\":\"54a5faac-00c4-4240-8c45-756db32a0620\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"The Japanese chose \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":19}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Kumārajīva\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":19,\"end\":29},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"05d4dcc1-b553-4d8a-b913-3d42e28773e0\",\"uuid\":\"d1fec17c-98fb-425c-8392-981a13955149\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"’s version for their translation, and the majority of modern translations have been based on this text. In 1962, Dr. E. Lamotte set forth to rectify this situation by basing his fine French translation on the Tibetan and the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":29,\"end\":254}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Xuanzang\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":254,\"end\":262},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"d4a6a09d-8d75-48cd-91f4-20308ea589fb\",\"uuid\":\"055c0ad2-ba7d-4e2f-993b-acc57830389a\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" versions. The history comes full circle finally, as the Rev. E. Bangert first translated the Tibetan into modern Thai and then into current Sanskrit.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":262,\"end\":412}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"2f81eb83-c3e4-4c5f-85c6-f15f0af233cf\",\"sort\":592,\"type\":\"introduction\",\"label\":\"i.17\",\"alignments\":{}},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":692,\"uuid\":\"2f81eb83-c3e4-4c5f-85c6-f15f0af233cf\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"My translation is based on the Tibetan version, as I am most at home in that language, although at times the simplicity of the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":127}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Kumārajīva\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":127,\"end\":137},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"05d4dcc1-b553-4d8a-b913-3d42e28773e0\",\"uuid\":\"f4c3fc10-c9cb-4337-b6be-f05e3b3b6c5f\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", the psychological precision of \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":137,\"end\":170}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Xuanzang\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":170,\"end\":178},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"d4a6a09d-8d75-48cd-91f4-20308ea589fb\",\"uuid\":\"98f1c299-5159-4ebf-abfd-9711e2345f1a\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", or the elegance of Lamotte may have clarified the Tibetan, provided an alternative, or given me another reference point from which to find a middle way. Any significant departures from the basic Tibetan have been duly noted. The recently discovered Sanskrit text of the sūtra only came to light thirty years after the first edition of this translation was published, but was consulted for this new edition and has helped to make some of the revisions, including the updating of a number of Sanskrit proper names.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":178,\"end\":692}}]}]}],\"body\":[{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"b7c3bbe3-5035-4248-a585-1199872fc142\",\"sort\":601,\"type\":\"translationHeader\",\"label\":null,\"alignments\":{}},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"heading\",\"attrs\":{\"level\":2,\"start\":0,\"end\":15,\"uuid\":\"e7ee6495-9471-4df3-a2d9-914740279977\",\"class\":\"section-title\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"The Translation\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":15}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"f472cecb-f37f-4be5-96f5-1927cf3abb92\",\"sort\":602,\"type\":\"translation\",\"label\":\"\",\"alignments\":{\"toh176\":{\"folioUuid\":\"7395b84a-b9ac-4247-8e25-ad6ee5298346\",\"toh\":\"toh176\",\"tibetan\":\"༄༅༅། །རྒྱ་གར་སྐད་དུ། ཨཱརྱ་བི་མ་ལ་ཀཱིར་ཏི་ནིར་དེ་ཤ་ནཱ་མ་མ་ཧཱ་ཡཱ་ན་སཱུ་ཏྲ། བོད་སྐད་དུ། འཕགས་པ་དྲི་མ་མེད་པར་གྲགས་པས་བསྟན་པ་ཞེས་བྱ་བ་ཐེག་པ་ཆེན་པོའི་མདོ། \",\"folioNumber\":175,\"volumeNumber\":60}}},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"heading\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":25,\"uuid\":\"5ea7e869-467f-415a-b532-26078dd1540b\",\"level\":2,\"class\":\"body-title-honorific\",\"hasLeadingSpace\":true,\"leadingSpaceUuid\":\"a4c1233d-0e34-448b-909b-cf128280cb2b\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"The Noble Mahāyāna Sūtra \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":25}}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":25,\"end\":52,\"uuid\":\"96319081-3876-4ee3-93bb-85323aee887d\",\"level\":2,\"class\":\"body-title-main\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"The Teaching of Vimalakīrti\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":25,\"end\":52}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"86e5993e-8f51-4d70-b94b-679bfa3a9422\",\"sort\":603,\"type\":\"translationHeader\",\"label\":\"1.\",\"alignments\":{}},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"heading\",\"attrs\":{\"level\":3,\"start\":0,\"end\":41,\"uuid\":\"f0c32526-37d8-44e6-9a98-785044220bfe\",\"class\":\"section-title\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Chapter 1 Purification of the Buddhafield\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":41}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"08e1b91e-b9ca-41b6-85ed-6fc2fb15f7f7\",\"sort\":608,\"type\":\"translation\",\"label\":\"1.1\",\"alignments\":{\"toh176\":{\"folioUuid\":\"7395b84a-b9ac-4247-8e25-ad6ee5298346\",\"toh\":\"toh176\",\"tibetan\":\"སངས་རྒྱས་དང་། བྱང་ཆུབ་སེམས་དཔའ་དང་། འཕགས་པ་ཉན་ཐོས་དང་། རང་\\nསངས་རྒྱས་འདས་པ་དང་། ད་ལྟར་གྱི་དང་། མ་བྱོན་པ་ཐམས་ཅད་ལ་ཕྱག་འཚལ་ལོ། །\",\"folioNumber\":175,\"volumeNumber\":60}}},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":123,\"uuid\":\"08e1b91e-b9ca-41b6-85ed-6fc2fb15f7f7\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Reverence to all the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":21}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"buddhas\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":21,\"end\":28},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"9b76e3ce-41f6-4da3-89a2-722141c90c1e\",\"uuid\":\"d4fbba46-efbe-4023-9665-b83befcb7105\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":28,\"end\":30}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"bodhisattvas\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":30,\"end\":42},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"c72eb4f3-700e-454d-996e-5ccdba29e6be\",\"uuid\":\"4d44c662-91aa-4a9d-8f48-26e128db04fc\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":42,\"end\":44}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"noble disciples\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":44,\"end\":59},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"0f06ed1e-e4b7-40e4-acd7-d58e27e71907\",\"uuid\":\"c9b198c7-6e75-4064-bb7b-305711e98ffd\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", and \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":59,\"end\":65}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"pratyekabuddhas\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":65,\"end\":80},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"016a95f6-6eed-41e7-a916-3b9098b27158\",\"uuid\":\"b11ac5f7-48a8-4780-b245-53524cc7e13e\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", in the past, the present, and the future.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":80,\"end\":123}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"e7af7864-267e-45ba-8701-d0197961a7e8\",\"sort\":618,\"type\":\"translation\",\"label\":\"1.2\",\"alignments\":{\"toh176\":{\"folioUuid\":\"7395b84a-b9ac-4247-8e25-ad6ee5298346\",\"toh\":\"toh176\",\"tibetan\":\"འདི་སྐད་བདག་གིས་ཐོས་པ་དུས་གཅིག་ན། བཅོམ་ལྡན་འདས་ཡངས་པའི་གྲོང་ཁྱེར་ན་ཨ་མྲ་སྲུང་བའི་ཚལ་ན། དགེ་སློང་བརྒྱད་སྟོང་གི་དགེ་སློང་གི་དགེ་འདུན་ཆེན་པོ་དང་ཐབས་ཅིག་ཏུ་\\nབཞུགས་ཏེ། ཐམས་ཅད་ཀྱང་དགྲ་བཅོམ་པ། ཟག་པ་ཟད་པ། ཉོན་མོངས་པ་མེད་པ། དབང་དང་ལྡན་པར་གྱུར་པ། སེམས་ཤིན་ཏུ་རྣམ་པར་གྲོལ་བ། ཤེས་རབ་ཤིན་ཏུ་རྣམ་པར་གྲོལ་བ། ཅང་ཤེས་པ། གླང་པོ་ཆེན་པོ། བྱ་བ་བྱས་པ། བྱེད་པ་བྱས་པ། ཁུར་བོར་བ། བདག་\\nགི་དོན་རྗེས་སུ་ཐོབ་པ། སྲིད་པར་ཀུན་ཏུ་སྦྱོར་བ་ཡོངས་སུ་ཟད་པ། ཡང་དག་པའི་ཤེས་པས་སེམས་ཤིན་ཏུ་རྣམ་པར་གྲོལ་བ། སེམས་ཀྱི་དབང་ཐམས་ཅད་ཀྱི་དམ་པའི་ཕ་རོལ་དུ་སོན་པ་ཤ་སྟག་གོ། །\",\"folioNumber\":175,\"volumeNumber\":60}}},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":691,\"uuid\":\"e7af7864-267e-45ba-8701-d0197961a7e8\",\"hasLeadingSpace\":true,\"leadingSpaceUuid\":\"51afecfd-265c-452a-8d63-ff805da3ae04\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Thus did I hear on a single occasion. The \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":42}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Lord\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":42,\"end\":46},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"41c623b8-3d94-4f8e-b2c5-1d7a5f5af6d3\",\"uuid\":\"59820703-fa2c-4a5f-b516-38ca4877dfc0\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":46,\"end\":47}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Buddha\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":47,\"end\":53},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"9b76e3ce-41f6-4da3-89a2-722141c90c1e\",\"uuid\":\"58da5790-07b0-460a-b248-2a11878c8497\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" was in residence in the garden of \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":53,\"end\":88}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Āmrapālī\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":88,\"end\":96},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"837c2527-85cb-4a76-bf21-913ecb4a5d69\",\"uuid\":\"676838ec-286d-41c7-8171-f2e02c67132f\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", in the city of \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":96,\"end\":113}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Vaiśālī\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":113,\"end\":120},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"e9c61804-d922-4a99-88ea-836faa6fd3c4\",\"uuid\":\"6aa69033-6621-4c80-b8cb-231d39720921\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", attended by a great gathering. Of \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":120,\"end\":156}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"bhikṣus\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":156,\"end\":163},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"700a47fd-7018-450b-b636-4ceaea2b8574\",\"uuid\":\"dc4594db-9952-4ca5-9ad5-db0c07e1c598\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" there were eight thousand, all \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":163,\"end\":195}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"arhats\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":195,\"end\":201},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"8584345b-bf7d-481b-ac82-4146d2374b3c\",\"uuid\":\"a81652e4-9743-4cdb-bfbb-3948fa08dd20\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\". They were free from impurities and \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":201,\"end\":238}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"afflictions\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":238,\"end\":249},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"62aa0bc0-1ed1-49a6-b18e-9b0f37c6aeef\",\"uuid\":\"355d6787-0987-4511-b749-7c968d686b5a\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", and all had attained self-mastery. Their minds were entirely liberated by perfect knowledge. They were calm and dignified, like royal elephants. They had accomplished their work, done what they had to do, cast off their burdens, attained their goals, and totally destroyed the bonds of existence. Their true knowledge had made their minds entirely free. They all had attained the utmost perfection of every form of control over their minds.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":249,\"end\":691},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"endNoteLink\",\"attrs\":{\"notes\":[{\"endNote\":\"04455931-6938-4014-b817-b0250d6c2696\",\"label\":\"14\",\"uuid\":\"cbdcf073-706f-484f-8831-a3a96cdd3105\",\"start\":691,\"end\":691,\"location\":\"end\",\"toh\":null}]}}]}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"1de2ed05-edeb-43c0-b980-f7c0447fa835\",\"sort\":637,\"type\":\"translation\",\"label\":\"1.3\",\"alignments\":{\"toh176\":{\"folioUuid\":\"7395b84a-b9ac-4247-8e25-ad6ee5298346\",\"toh\":\"toh176\",\"tibetan\":\"བྱང་ཆུབ་སེམས་དཔའ་སུམ་ཁྲི་ཉིས་སྟོང་དང་ཡང་ཐབས་ཅིག་སྟེ། མངོན་པར་ཤེས་\\nཔ་མངོན་པར་ཤེས་པའི་བྱང་ཆུབ་སེམས་དཔའ་སེམས་དཔའ་ཆེན་པོ་མངོན་པར་ཤེས་པ་ཆེན་པོ་ཡོངས་སུ་སྦྱངས་པ་ལས་ངེས་པར་བྱུང་བ། སངས་རྒྱས་ཀྱིས་བྱིན་གྱི་རླབས་ཀྱིས་བྱིན་གྱིས་བརླབས་པ། ཆོས་ཀྱི་གྲོང་ཁྱེར་སྲུང་བ། དམ་པའི་ཆོས་ཡོངས་སུ་འཛིན་པ། སེང་གེའི་སྒྲ་ཆེན་པོ་སྒྲོགས་པ། \\nཕྱོགས་བཅུར་སྒྲ་ཤིན་ཏུ་བསྒྲགས་པ། གསོལ་བ་མ་བཏབ་པར་སེམས་ཅན་ཐམས་ཅད་ཀྱི་དགེ་བའི་བཤེས་གཉེན་དུ་གྱུར་པ། དཀོན་མཆོག་གསུམ་གྱི་རིགས་རྒྱུན་མི་འཆད་པར་བྱེད་པ། བདུད་དང་ཕྱིར་རྒོལ་བ་བཅོམ་པ་ཕ་རོལ་གྱི་རྒོལ་བ་ཐམས་ཅད་ཀྱི་ཟིལ་གྱིས་མི་ནོན་པ། \",\"folioNumber\":175,\"volumeNumber\":60}}},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":597,\"uuid\":\"1de2ed05-edeb-43c0-b980-f7c0447fa835\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Of \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":3}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"bodhisattvas\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":3,\"end\":15},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"c72eb4f3-700e-454d-996e-5ccdba29e6be\",\"uuid\":\"600d65f7-24cc-45a9-be11-95c80784c02f\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" there were thirty-two thousand, \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":15,\"end\":48}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"great spiritual heroes\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":48,\"end\":70},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"8f291152-70ba-4e56-9a1c-8d800b7f67e6\",\"uuid\":\"ecf27dab-9862-435c-97bc-b495408d5c8d\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" who were universally acclaimed. They were dedicated through the penetrating activity of their great \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":70,\"end\":171}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"superknowledges\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":171,\"end\":186},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"6b6440dd-6d95-46dd-9c77-9f9241f4e84a\",\"uuid\":\"933f87ba-a52e-4bd9-81cc-d6a1d0b8d22a\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" and were sustained by the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":186,\"end\":213}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"grace\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":213,\"end\":218},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"8de0a524-74ca-4f51-8f2e-ba02b9f037a2\",\"uuid\":\"08530a52-b995-413a-a3a3-b599b47a856d\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" of the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":218,\"end\":226}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Buddha\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":226,\"end\":232},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"9b76e3ce-41f6-4da3-89a2-722141c90c1e\",\"uuid\":\"181bf6a3-95a5-456c-b8a1-f81a3c717430\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\". Guardians of the city of \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":232,\"end\":259}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Dharma\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":259,\"end\":265},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"c08db6f5-393e-4ec4-bf72-4043e53b3129\",\"uuid\":\"1d61329d-6e69-4bdb-8e9e-8e7413c00833\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", they upheld the true doctrine,\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":265,\"end\":297},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"endNoteLink\",\"attrs\":{\"notes\":[{\"endNote\":\"5cb78ab3-7bab-4412-a1ec-7a8642d4b29f\",\"label\":\"15\",\"uuid\":\"eec5d188-c668-42b3-b4d1-a6a885c74df9\",\"start\":297,\"end\":297,\"location\":\"end\",\"toh\":null}]}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" and their great teachings resounded like the lion’s roar throughout the ten directions. Without having to be asked, they were the natural \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":297,\"end\":436}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"spiritual benefactors\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":436,\"end\":457},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"e5303c16-abe1-4662-81c1-ccb782cc20f3\",\"uuid\":\"e97a8c73-9dec-49aa-ab62-6943f80f7af6\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" of all living beings. They maintained unbroken the succession of the Three Jewels, conquering devils and foes and overwhelming all critics.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":457,\"end\":597}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"13fb1fb2-3a2e-4282-9042-7bec9f1cf717\",\"sort\":655,\"type\":\"translation\",\"label\":\"1.4\",\"alignments\":{\"toh176\":{\"folioUuid\":\"7395b84a-b9ac-4247-8e25-ad6ee5298346\",\"toh\":\"toh176\",\"tibetan\":\"དྲན་པ་དང་། \\nབློ་གྲོས་དང་། རྟོགས་པ་དང་། ཏིང་ངེ་འཛིན་དང་། གཟུངས་དང་། སྤོབས་པ་ཕུན་སུམ་ཚོགས་པ། སྒྲིབ་པ་དང་ཀུན་ནས་སྡང་བ་ཐམས་ཅད་དང་བྲལ་བ། སྒྲིབ་པ་མེད་པའི་རྣམ་པར་ཐར་པ་ལ་གནས་པ། སྤོབས་པ་རྒྱུན་མི་འཆད་པ་སྦྱིན་པ་དང་། དུལ་བ་དང་། མི་འགྱུར་བ་དང་། ཡང་[F.175.b]དག་པར་སྡོམ་པ་དང་། ཚུལ་ཁྲིམས་དང་། བཟོད་པ་དང་། བརྩོན་འགྲུས་དང་། བསམ་གཏན་དང་། ཤེས་རབ་དང་། ཐབས་ལ་མཁས་པ་དང་། སྨོན་ལམ་དང་། སྟོབས་དང་། ཡེ་ཤེས་ཀྱི་ཕ་རོལ་ཏུ་ཕྱིན་པ་ལས་ངེས་པར་བྱུང་བ། མི་དམིགས་པ་དང་མི་སྐྱེ་བའི་ཆོས་ལ་བཟོད་པ་དང་ལྡན་པ། ཕྱིར་མི་ལྡོག་\\nཔའི་ཆོས་ཀྱི་འཁོར་ལོ་སྐོར་བ། མཚན་ཉིད་མེད་པའི་ཕྱག་རྒྱས་བཏབ་པ། \",\"folioNumber\":175,\"volumeNumber\":60}}},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":628,\"uuid\":\"13fb1fb2-3a2e-4282-9042-7bec9f1cf717\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Their mindfulness, intelligence, realization, \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":46}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"meditation\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":46,\"end\":56},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"72ea6449-0c42-401c-bff0-be87bffdfd07\",\"uuid\":\"0467124f-f19b-461b-a4ac-7d17740bb7fc\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":56,\"end\":58}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"retention\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":58,\"end\":67},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"e6cb9fdd-cfe1-4188-8cfb-b72314d72e94\",\"uuid\":\"6f694322-2baa-4dfa-99e7-e7e2e61b6e84\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", and eloquence all were perfected. They were free of all obscurations and emotional involvements, living in \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":67,\"end\":176}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"liberation\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":176,\"end\":186},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"1f6de051-60d0-418f-9255-9634be3f22b8\",\"uuid\":\"1d7a2cc5-10f5-45a4-9184-11b755d25b97\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" without impediment. They were totally dedicated through the transcendences of generosity; subdued, unwavering, and sincere \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":186,\"end\":310}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"morality\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":310,\"end\":318},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"324d8870-bad2-4237-a723-c4203312fb79\",\"uuid\":\"4a35569f-2d6b-4786-bd3d-4b4983722b7b\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"; tolerance; effort; \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":318,\"end\":339}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"meditation\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":339,\"end\":349},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"72ea6449-0c42-401c-bff0-be87bffdfd07\",\"uuid\":\"b0472f45-2996-4309-abea-7b544d6a6d12\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"; \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":349,\"end\":351}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"wisdom\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":351,\"end\":357},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"38971298-6f62-48f0-b271-36261568d441\",\"uuid\":\"afb91f1c-92df-4b43-9655-0d87abf2a574\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"; skill in \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":357,\"end\":368}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"liberative art\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":368,\"end\":382},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"7c541c84-ac9d-49ce-92dc-9b1f6912648d\",\"uuid\":\"eef9a6a3-0dfb-45fb-9010-3d7ea452a4fe\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"; commitment; power; and \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":382,\"end\":407}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"gnosis\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":407,\"end\":413},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"57f30533-44ff-42b7-a670-f57da1f54504\",\"uuid\":\"3c5077b3-a546-4f6a-bc69-1bfa0243c934\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\".\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":413,\"end\":414},\"marks\"